The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Infotech titans bet big on city

 SOHINI MOOKHERJEA

 CALL COUNTER

 Calcutta, July 7: Infotech biggies are bullish about their growth prospects in the city. Tata Consultancy Services plans to treble its headcount in three years and Cognizant Technology Solutions will hire 2,200 more professionals for its leased space here.

 Genpact, Indias largest BPO, adds at least 50 employees a month in Calcutta. It is also in the final stages of closing a deal for its 5-7-acre special economic zone in New Town, Rajarhat. Companies like HCL Infosystems, HSBC and Rolta have asked for land to either expand or start operations in the city.

 TCS is very optimistic about the city. It shows in the companys plan to increase its headcount from 7,000 to 20,000 in three years. Since companies such as TCS and Cognizant have a positive outlook on the city, others are also looking to setting up base here, said Siddharth, principal secretary in the Bengal IT department.

 Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu, the worlds second-largest professional services company, recently started a unit in the city and will offer its full range of services including tax consulting and financial advisory services for its eastern region and national clients. The company will set up a facility in Salt Lakes Sector V with 100 employees. 




